First, let's convert the mixed number into an improper fraction. $8\frac{1}{3}$ is equivalent to $\frac{25}{3}$. Now, we can multiply $6$ by $\frac{25}{3}$.
\begin{align*}6 \cdot \frac{25}{3} &= \frac{6 \cdot 25}{3} \\ &= \frac{150}{3} \\ &= 50\end{align*}
<answer>50</answer>

